Actually, I'm a pretty spiritual person.  I don't believe in *organized* religion.  The religion of man.  I grew up Southern Baptist.  Yes, I have seen some excesses in the Church. <br>
<br>
However, unlike Louis Pascal, I don't think it is in a persons best interests to blindly accept a faith without question.  Is it better to worship God than not at all?  What if the &quot;God&quot; you are worshipping isn't a good god?  What if you are actually worshipping the devil?<br>
<br>
The Christian religion asks me to accept everything on &quot;faith&quot; but I only see damning facts.  Maybe the early Christian movement has some merit but the current version of Christianity that most of Western Civ practices is a far cry from &quot;civilized&quot; in my opinion.<br>
<br>
 <p>Herder
